    "description": "Ichimasa Kamaboko Co., Ltd. produces and sells fish-paste products in Japan. It operates through Seafood Paste Products and Prepared Food Business, Mushroom Business, and Transportation and Warehousing segments. The company offers frozen cooked fish cakes, frozen deep fried fish cakes, jumbo crab sticks, seafood sea urchins, sea salads, marine sticks, and naruto and chikuwa products. It also provides prepared side dishes, including goma dofu; snack food, such as sardine chips; maitake mushrooms; and freight transportation and warehousing services. The company sells its products to supermarkets, drug stores, and other retailers. It exports its products. Ichimasa Kamaboko Co., Ltd. was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Niigata, Japan."
